Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title,90210 is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television.The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000,,and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.
The initial premise of the show was based on the adjustment and culture shock that twins Brandon (Jason Priestley) and Brenda Walsh (Shannen Doherty) experienced when they and their parents, Jim (James Eckhouse) and Cindy (Carol Potter), moved from Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Beverly Hills, California.[6][7] In addition to chronicling the characters' friendships and romantic relationships, the show addressed topical issues such as sex, date rape, homophobia, animal rights, alcoholism, drug abuse, domestic violence, eating disorders, racism (including antisemitism), teenage suicide, teenage pregnancy, and AIDS.

title: BEVERLY HILLS 90210, 1990 Cast Then And Now 2022 How They Changed.
description:
BEVERLY HILLS 90210, 1990 Cast Then And Now 2022 How They Changed.

Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title, 90210 is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television. The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000, and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in the upscale and star-studded community of Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.

The initial premise of the show was based on the adjustment and culture shock that twins Brandon (Jason Priestley) and Brenda Walsh (Shannen Doherty) experienced when they and their parents, Jim (James Eckhouse) and Cindy (Carol Potter), moved from Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Beverly Hills, California.In addition to chronicling the characters' friendships and romantic relationships, the show addressed topical issues such as sex, date rape, homophobia, animal rights, alcoholism, drug abuse, domestic violence, eating disorders, antisemitism, racism, teenage suicide, teenage pregnancy, and AIDS.

After poor ratings during its first season, the series gained popularity during the summer of 1991, when Fox aired a special "summer season" of the show while most other series were in reruns.Viewership increased dramatically, and 90210 became one of Fox's top shows when it returned that fall. The show became a global pop culture phenomenon with its cast members, particularly Jason Priestley and Luke Perry, who became teen idols; the series also made actresses Shannen Doherty and Jennie Garth household names in the United States. The show is credited with creating or popularizing the teen soap genre that many other successful television shows followed in the years to come.

The show had many cast changes; Jennie Garth, Tori Spelling, Brian Austin Green, and Ian Ziering were the only actors to appear during its entire run and appeared on the first episode of the spin-off Melrose Place.

On February 27, 2019, it was announced that a six-episode reboot has been ordered by Fox and that the show would simply be titled BH90210. On May 8, 2019, it was announced that the reboot would premiere on August 7, 2019, at 9/8c on Fox.

title: Watch Fox's BH90210 Trailer | Beverly Hills Reboot
description:
Shannen Doherty, Jason Priestley, Jennie Garth, Ian Ziering, Gabrielle Carteris, Brian Austin Green, and Tori Spelling have all reunited for this meta version of BH90210. They play themselves 19 years after the teen soap that launched their careers ended. In this heightened version of reality, when one of them suggests they join the reboot/revival frenzy and get the gang back together for a revival of 90210, naturally the whole cast is eager to sign on. You can definitely expect some good laughs and a lot of wistful sentimentality from this... parody revival. BH90210 premieres Wednesday, Aug. 7 at 9/8c on Fox.

BEVERLY HILLS, 90210 1990 Cast Then and Now 2022 How They Changed

Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title, 90210) is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television. The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000, and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.

title: Beverly Hills 90210 (1990 vs 2024) Cast: Then and Now
Beverly Hills, 90210 Cast: Allora e adesso (33 anni dopo) 1990 â€“ 2023
description:
Da Beverly Hills 1990 a Beverly Hills 2023: Il Fascino Senza Tempo dei Personaggi Iconici

Benvenuti a bordo di un viaggio affascinante attraverso il tempo, dove faremo un confronto epocale tra due diverse epoche di Beverly Hills e dei suoi indimenticabili abitanti. Questo video ci porterÃ  indietro al 1990, quando Beverly Hills 90210 ha fatto la sua prima comparsa sulla scena televisiva, e ci condurrÃ  nel 2023, permettendoci di vedere come i personaggi che tanto abbiamo amato siano cambiati nel corso di oltre due decenni di avventure, drammi, e intrighi.

Nel 1990, abbiamo conosciuto Brenda e Brandon Walsh, Kelly Taylor, Dylan McKay, e tanti altri, mentre affrontavano le sfide dell'adolescenza e dell'etÃ  adulta nella prestigiosa Beverly Hills High School. I loro abiti, i loro pettinati, e le loro storie sono diventati parte della cultura popolare, creando un legame profondo con il pubblico di tutto il mondo.

Ora, nel 2023, ci troveremo di nuovo in questa affascinante cittÃ  californiana per vedere come i nostri amati personaggi abbiano affrontato il passare del tempo. Cosa Ã¨ successo nelle loro vite? Come sono cambiati nel corso degli anni? Quali nuove sfide hanno dovuto affrontare e come sono diventati adulti?

Questo video non Ã¨ solo un viaggio nella trasformazione fisica dei personaggi, ma anche un'occasione per riflettere su quanto sia speciale il legame che abbiamo con questi personaggi televisivi. Sono diventati parte della nostra storia personale e ci hanno accompagnato attraverso momenti di gioia e di tristezza.

Abbiamo creato questo video con amore e dedizione, e ora vi chiediamo di unirvi a noi in questa esperienza unica. Condividete i vostri pensieri, le vostre emozioni, e le vostre preferenze nei commenti qui sotto. Ci piacerebbe sapere quale versione di Beverly Hills e dei suoi personaggi preferite, e come questa serie televisiva ha influenzato la vostra vita nel corso degli anni.

Grazie per essere con noi in questo incredibile viaggio nel tempo. Preparatevi a immergervi nel fascino senza tempo di Beverly Hills e a riscoprire la magia di questi personaggi iconici. Non vediamo l'ora di leggere le vostre storie e di condividere questa straordinaria esperienza con voi.

title: BEVERLY HILLS 90210 Reunion Panel â€“ Steel City Con April 2024
description:
Beverly Hills 90210 stars Tori Spelling, Ian Ziering, Shannen Doherty, Jason Priestly, Jennie Garth, Brian Austin Green, and Gabrielle Carteris came together for a panel at Steel City Con to talk about the show, their experiences, and to answer fan questions.

Tori Spelling played Donna Martin on Beverly Hills 90210, and is also known for Scary Movie 2, The House of Yes, Trick, BH90210, Mystery Girls, Smallville, The Last Sharknado: Itâ€™s About Time, and more.

Ian Ziering was Steve Sanders on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for Sharknado, Swamp Thing, Biker Mice from Mars, Mighty Ducks: The Animated Series, Guiding Light, and more.

Shannen Doherty portrayed Brenda Walsh on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for Charmed, Heathers, Mallrats, 90210, North Shore, Almost Dead, and many more.

Jason Priestly played Brandon Walsh on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for Private Eyes, Call Me Fitz, Raising Expectations, Wishenproof, Side Order of Life, and many more.

Jennie Garth portrayed Kelly Taylor on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for What I Like About You, Girl Positive, Secret Santa, Mystery Girls, A Christmas Wedding Tail, The Street, and more.

Brian Austin Green played David Silver on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for Knots Landing, Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles, Fish Without a Bicycle, Anger Management, The Conners, and more.

Gabrielle Carteris was Andrea Zuckerman on Beverly Hills 90210 and is also known for Raising Cain, Minority Report, Code Black, Marvel: Ultimate Alliance, Batman: The Brave and the Bold, Another World, and more.

This panel was recorded on April 13th, 2024.

Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title, 90210) is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television. The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000, and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.

The initial premise of the show was based on the adjustment and culture shock that twins Brandon (Jason Priestley) and Brenda Walsh (Shannen Doherty) experienced when they and their parents, Jim (James Eckhouse) and Cindy (Carol Potter), moved from Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Beverly Hills, California. In addition to chronicling the characters' friendships and romantic relationships, the show addressed topical issues such as sex, date rape, homophobia, animal rights, alcoholism, drug abuse, domestic violence, eating disorders, antisemitism, racism, teenage suicide, teenage pregnancy, and AIDS.

After poor ratings during its first season, the series gained popularity during the summer of 1991, when Fox aired a special "summer season" of the show while most other series were in reruns. Viewership increased dramatically, and 90210 became one of Fox's top shows when it returned that fall. The show became a global pop culture phenomenon with its cast members, particularly Jason Priestley and Luke Perry, who became teen idols; the series also made actresses Shannen Doherty and Jennie Garth household names in the United States. The show is credited with creating or popularizing the teen soap genre that many other successful television shows followed in the years to come.

The show had many cast changes; Jennie Garth, Tori Spelling, Brian Austin Green, and Ian Ziering were the only actors to appear during its entire run and appeared on the first episode of the spin-off Melrose Place.

On February 27, 2019, it was announced that a six-episode reboot had been ordered by Fox and that the show would simply be titled BH90210. On May 8, 2019, it was announced that the reboot would premiere on August 7, 2019, at 9/8c on Fox.

title: John E. Davis - Beverly Hills, 90210 Theme (Guitars & Drum) (MrDyzzoink)
description:
This is a rearrangement of a very super hip catchy tune from the 90s.
To be honest, I never really followed the story line.
I guess it was about people saying things to each other at that address very often.

Like, hey, you again.
Uh huh, of course. I live here, don't I?
No. Why do you look like that?
Like what?
That.
Then for no reason, third person walked in and sat upside down and fourth guy jumped into a pool with huge shining teeth. 
And such other hypnosis method.

Melrose Place for example, *waving head*, you *garbled message* plastic face.

Aside the soap in the opera, but rarely shower scene or dish washing or full 1 hour laundry set, the sweet music was composed by John E. Davis.

Thanks for watching and reading this brief extraordinaire description.

For backing track of my rearrangement go to: https://revo.johanpaul.net/music/backingtracks#90210

Airwolf is almost like that. People saying things to each other. But it took place in the bottom of a canyon, sometimes an office, sometimes bar, etc, instead of Beverly Hills, 90210 address.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CzwVFNYQmtQ

title: Beverly Hills, 90210 Intro 1990
description:
Siguenos en: http://www.facebook.com/retro80sy90s

Beverly Hills, 90210 fue una serie con formato de telenovela juvenil emitida desde el 4 de octubre de 1990 al 17 de mayo de 2000 en el horario de mayor audiencia de la cadena FOX de los Estados Unidos y posteriormente en varias cadenas alrededor del mundo. La serie trataba sobre la vida de un grupo de adolescentes que vivÃ­an en la lujosa y acomodada comunidad de Beverly Hills, California y asistÃ­an a la escuela ficticia de secundaria West Beverly Hills High School y luego a la tambiÃ©n ficticia California University. El show fue creado por Darren Star y producido por Aaron Spelling. El "90210" en el tÃ­tulo se refiere a uno de los cÃ³digos postales de la zona (o cÃ³digo ZIP).
En un principio los protagonistas principales eran los hermanos mellizos Walsh, Brandon (interpretado por Jason Priestley) y Brenda (interpretada por Shannen Doherty), que se mudaron con sus padres, Jim y Cindy, de Wayzata, Minnesota, un suburbio de Minneapolis, a Beverly Hills. De todos modos, al pasar el tiempo, esta se enfocÃ³ en otros aspectos de la actualidad juvenil californiana tales como violaciones durante citas amorosas, el alcoholismo, el abuso de drogas, el suicidio de adolescentes y el embarazo precoz, dejando de lado el formato inicial.
La serie ganÃ³ popularidad durante el verano del 1991, cuando FOX transmitiÃ³ un especial llamado "temporada de verano", mientras la mayorÃ­a de las series se encontraban en el acostumbrado descanso veraniego. Al comenzar el otoÃ±o en los Estados Unidos, la serie se habÃ­a convertido en una de las mÃ¡s populares de la cadena FOX. Los seguidores de la serie se incrementaron dramÃ¡ticamente y los miembros de elenco, particularmente Jason Priestley y Luke Perry, se convirtieron en Ã­dolos juveniles, mientras que las actrices Shannen Doherty, Jennie Garth y Tori Spelling se volvieron nombres muy conocidos en la televisiÃ³n estadounidense.

title: ðŸŽ¬Celebrity Deaths... Beverly Hills, 90210 Actress Shannen Doherty ðŸ•ŠR.I.PðŸ•Š
description:
ðŸŽ¬Actress... Children: None

Marital status: Married 

Shannen Maria Doherty (April 12, 1971 â€“ July 13, 2024) was an American actress who played roles in both television and film, including Jenny Wilder in Little House on the Prairie (1982â€“1983), Maggie Malene in Girls Just Want to Have Fun (1985), Kris Witherspoon in Our House (1986â€“1988), Heather Duke in Heathers (1989), Brenda Walsh in Beverly Hills, 90210 (1990â€“1994), 90210 (2008â€“2009) and BH90210 (2019), Prue Halliwell in Charmed (1998â€“2001), and Dobbs in Fortress (2021).

In 1982, Doherty had guest spots on TV series, including Voyagers! and Father Murphy, which was created and produced by Michael Landon. The same year, 11-year-old Doherty won the recurring role of Jenny Wilder on Little House on the Prairie, which Landon starred in and produced. Doherty appeared in all but four episodes in the final season of the show, which was canceled in 1983.

Doherty lent her voice to the animated film The Secret of NIMH in 1982. She appeared in an episode of Magnum, P.I. ("A Sense of Debt"), followed by an early episode of Airwolf ("Bite Of The Jackal"), for which she was nominated as Best Young Actress: Guest in a Series at the 6th Youth in Film Awards in 1984.

Shannen Maria Doherty was born in Memphis, Tennessee, to Tom and Rosa Doherty. She was raised in her mother's Southern Baptist faith. She was of Irish and Native American descent.

title: Beverly Hills 90210 (1990) Cast Then and Now (2024)
description:
Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title, 90210) is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television. The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000, and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.

The initial premise of the show was based on the adjustment and culture shock that twins Brandon (Jason Priestley) and Brenda Walsh (Shannen Doherty) experienced when they and their parents, Jim (James Eckhouse) and Cindy (Carol Potter), moved from Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Beverly Hills, California. In addition to chronicling the characters' friendships and romantic relationships, the show addressed topical issues such as sex, date rape, homophobia, animal rights, alcoholism, drug abuse, domestic violence, eating disorders, racism (including antisemitism), teenage suicide, teenage pregnancy, and AIDS.

After poor ratings during its first season, the series gained popularity during the summer of 1991, when Fox aired a special "summer season" of the show while most other series were in reruns. Viewership increased dramatically, and 90210 became one of Fox's top shows when it returned that fall. The show became a global pop culture phenomenon with its cast members, particularly Jason Priestley and Luke Perry, who became teen idols; the series also made actresses Shannen Doherty and Jennie Garth household names in the United States. The show is credited with creating or popularizing the teen soap genre that many other successful television shows followed in the years to come.

The show had many cast changes; Jennie Garth, Tori Spelling, Brian Austin Green, and Ian Ziering were the only actors to appear during its entire run and appeared on the first episode of the spin-off Melrose Place.

On February 27, 2019, it was announced that a six-episode reboot had been ordered by Fox and that the show would simply be titled BH90210. The revival premiered on Fox on August 7, 2019, and was canceled on November 7, 2019.

title: Shannen Doherty, Star of Beverly Hills, 90210 and Charmed, Dies at 53 | PEOPLE
description:
Shannen Doherty has died after years of living with cancer, PEOPLE has confirmed. She was 53.

"It is with a heavy heart that I confirm the passing of actress Shannen Doherty. On Saturday, July 13, she lost her battle with cancer after many years of fighting the disease," Doherty's longtime publicist Leslie Sloane confirmed in an exclusive statement to PEOPLE on Sunday, July 14.

"The devoted daughter, sister, aunt and friend was surrounded by her loved ones as well as her dog, Bowie. The family asks for their privacy at this time so they can grieve in peace," Sloane continued.

The Beverly Hills 90210 star was first diagnosed with breast cancer in 2015 and spoke candidly to PEOPLE in November 2023 about her Stage 4 breast cancer, which had by then spread to her bones, saying at the time that she didn't "want to die."

â€œIâ€™m not done with living. Iâ€™m not done with loving. Iâ€™m not done with creating. Iâ€™m not done with hopefully changing things for the better,â€ she told PEOPLE. "Iâ€™m just not â€” Iâ€™m not done.â€

title: Classic TV Theme: Beverly Hills 90210 (Full Stereo) +Bonus!
description:
This 1990 series that ran for ten seasons almost didn't make it to sophomore year. The first go-round ranked at a miserable #88 so Fox execs tried a stunt: a special 'summer season' that debuted in July. That perked audience interest enough to get the show back on track, though it never actually cracked the top 40. The series garnered many 'Young Artist' awards, but the only Emmy nomination was for a guest star from an earlier era: Milton Berle. The theme is by John E Davis, whose first attempt got a thumbs down from Fox execs. They wanted a replacement 'by tomorrow' so Davis pulled an all-nighter and delivered. "There are two feels â€“ the rock and roll edge first, then at the end it turns a little sweeter, which was my homage to the family values of the show.â€ More on the theme and its signature clap-clap effect here - https://tinyurl.com/yd5pn5ek
0:00 Opening titles, season one.
1:26 Opening titles, season three.
2:51 Opening titles, season seven.
3:48 Opening titles, season ten.
4:46 End credits, season five.
5:34 BONUS: '90210' opening titles and end credits, season five. This 2008 spin-off aired on the CW. The minimalist treatment of Davis's theme is quite a contrast.
tags: TV Themes,Classic TV,Beverly Hills 90210,John E Davis

title: John E Davis - Beverly Hills 90210 Theme Song (Brian Armand Cover)
description:
My IMDb page:
http://www.imdb.com/name/nm9416962/

My Official Website:
http://www.themewaycreative.weebly.com

All music/instruments on my cover version were recorded, performed, mixed & mastered by myself, Brian Armand 2019.

I decided to record my cover of the original Beverly Hills ,90210 theme after I found out that BH90210 was coming out. I found out in the end of February, like most of us did, and got to work on my cover version, and released it in April that same year, 2019.

I wanted to pay homage to the old show I grew up and watched faithfully every week, and at the same time pay tribute to the new show that was yet to air. 

I paid close attention to the various seasons and how the theme, although for the most part stayed the same, subtle variations were added, taken out, etc, however the bulk of the theme has always stayed pretty much the same. So when it came time for me to create my cover version, I made my own variation from the different seasons. See if you can notice what inspired me from each season and how I worked it into my cover. The music on my cover is played and recorded entirely by myself, and my goal was to tryto make it sound as authentic and close to the original as possible. Thanks to John E. Davis for creating such a memorable masterpiece of a TV show theme that is recognizable the world over and to a 90s show that was and still is my #1 tv show of the 1990s!

Also, had fun recreating the logo for this cover version! Paying tribute to my favorite TV show of the 90s which featured an amazing cast and crew of talented individuals. Cheers to the whole 90210 family who are bringing back the show to network TV this summer! We'll be watching for sure!! :)

title: Actores de Beverly Hills 90210 que ya murieron
description:
Actores de Beverly Hills 90210 que ya murieron

Shannen Doherty

Este fin de semana se dio a conocer la muerte de la actriz Shannen Doherty, quien daba vida a Brenda, esto luego de una terrible batalla contra el cÃ¡ncer de mama y de huesos, que desde el aÃ±o pasado se habÃ­a convertido en metÃ¡stasis. 

Mediante un comunicado de prensa, su representante Leslie Sloane, dio a conocer la noticia: 

"Con gran pesar confirmo el fallecimiento de la actriz Shannen Doherty. El sÃ¡bado 13 de julio perdiÃ³ la batalla contra el cÃ¡ncer despuÃ©s de muchos aÃ±os de luchar contra la enfermedad. La devota hija, hermana, tÃ­a y amiga estaba rodeada de sus seres queridos y de su perro, Bowie. La familia pide su privacidad en este momento para poder llorar en pazâ€.

Luke Perry

El 4 de marzo de 2019, nos enteramos de la muerte de Luke Perry, quien daba vida a Dylan, un joven problemÃ¡tico en Beverly Hills 90210, debido a un derrame cerebral masivo mientras estaba descansando en su hogar en Sherman Oaks, California. 

En su Ãºltimo proyecto televisivo, Riverdale, su personaje Fred Andrews, muriÃ³ al ser atropellado por un extraÃ±o, por lo que la tristeza y lÃ¡grimas del elenco en su funeral en pantalla fueron reales. Ese mismo aÃ±o se estrenÃ³ la cinta Ã‰rase Una Vez En Hollywood, que realizÃ³ junto a Brad Pitt y Leonardo DiCaprio.

Joe E. Tata

Durante mÃ¡s de 230 episodios, Joe E. Tata dio vida a Nat Bussichio, el dueÃ±o del restaurante donde los protagonistas de la serie pasaban las tardes. En 2018 el intÃ©rprete fue diagnosticado con Alzheimer, y finalmente muriÃ³ el 24 de agosto de 2022 a los 85 aÃ±os.

Michelle Nicastro

Reconocida principalmente por ser parte del elenco de Xena: La Princesa Guerrera, Michelle Nicastro dio vida a Brandy en un episodio de la serie. El 4 de noviembre de 2010 muriÃ³ de cÃ¡ncer a la edad de 50 aÃ±os. 

Julie Parrish

Si el nombre de Julie Parrish te suena, es seguramente por su participaciÃ³n en la serie Star Trek, aunque durante su vida realizÃ³ mÃ¡s de 30 pelÃ­culas y series, en especial Beverly Hills 902010, en donde dio vida a Joan Diamond, la esposa de Nat, durante 8 episodios. Tras una larga lucha contra el cÃ¡ncer de ovario falleciÃ³ en Los Ãngeles en 2003.

Matthew Perry

Antes de alcanzar la fama por la serie Friends, Matthew Perry dio vida a Roger Azarian, un amigo millonario de Brandon en Beverly Hills 90210. El 28 de octubre de 2023, fue encontrado inconsciente en un jacuzzi de su casa en Los Ãngeles a los 54 aÃ±os de edad.

Aunque hasta el momento aÃºn no se conocen todos los detalles de su muerte, se ha dicho que fueron los efectos de la ketamina los que habrÃ­an complicado un problema de salud que ya tenÃ­a.

#beverlyhills90210 #90210 #california 

Beverly Hills, 90210 (often referred to by its short title, 90210 is an American teen drama television series created by Darren Star and produced by Aaron Spelling under his production company Spelling Television. The series ran for ten seasons on Fox from October 4, 1990, to May 17, 2000, and is the first of six television series in the Beverly Hills, 90210 franchise. The series follows the lives of a group of friends living in Beverly Hills, California, as they transition from high school to college and into the adult world. "90210" refers to one of the city's five ZIP codes.

The initial premise of the show was based on the adjustment and culture shock that twins Brandon (Jason Priestley) and Brenda Walsh (Shannen Doherty) experienced when they and their parents, Jim (James Eckhouse) and Cindy (Carol Potter), moved from Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Beverly Hills, California. In addition to chronicling the characters' friendships and romantic relationships, the show addressed topical issues such as sex, date rape, homophobia, animal rights, alcoholism, drug abuse, domestic violence, eating disorders, antisemitism, racism, teenage suicide, teenage pregnancy, and AIDS. 

After poor ratings during its first season, the series gained popularity during the summer of 1991, when Fox aired a special "summer season" of the show while most other series were in reruns. Viewership increased dramatically, and 90210 became one of Fox's top shows when it returned that fall. The show became a global pop culture phenomenon with its cast members, particularly Jason Priestley and Luke Perry, who became teen idols; the series also made actresses Shannen Doherty and Jennie Garth household names in the United States. The show is credited with creating or popularizing the teen soap genre that many other successful television shows followed in the years to come.

The show had many cast changes; Jennie Garth, Tori Spelling, Brian Austin Green, and Ian Ziering were the only actors to appear during its entire run and appeared on the first episode of the spin-off Melrose Place.

On February 27, 2019, it was announced that a six-episode reboot had been ordered by Fox and that the show would simply be titled BH90210. The revival premiered on Fox on August 7, 2019, and was cancelled on November 7, 2019.

The filming location for West Beverly High School was in the middle class community of Torrance at Torrance High School, located in the 90501 zip code. Torrance High can also be seen in other shows such as Buffy the Vampire Slayer.

Shannen Doherty Ã¨ morta a 53 anni dopo una lunga battaglia contro il cancro al seno. Nota per il suo ruolo di Brenda in Beverly Hills 90210, l'attrice ha condiviso apertamente il suo calvario con la malattia, diagnosticata per la prima volta nel 2015. A gennaio di quest'anno, Doherty aveva iniziato una nuova cura per il cancro al quarto stadio con metastasi alle ossa e al cervello. Nonostante la terapia inizialmente sembrasse inefficace, ha mostrato segni di miglioramento, che lei stessa ha definito un miracolo. Con uno spirito positivo, Doherty aveva imparato a vivere ogni giorno come un dono. L'annuncio della sua scomparsa Ã¨ stato dato da Leslie Sloane, che ha chiesto privacy per la famiglia in questo momento difficile.

Shannen Doherty died after a lengthy battle with stage 4 cancer. She was 53.

â€œIt is with a heavy heart that I confirm the passing of actress Shannen Doherty. On Saturday, July 13, she lost her battle with cancer after many years of fighting the disease,â€ her longtime publicist, Leslie Sloane, told People in a statement on Sunday.

â€œThe devoted daughter, sister, aunt and friend was surrounded by her loved ones as well as her dog, Bowie. The family asks for their privacy at this time so they can grieve in peace,â€ Sloane continued.

description:
La serie TV Beverly Hills 90210 ha rappresentato un cult per la generazione degli anni 90. Personaggi come Brandon, Brenda (avevano fantasia in famiglia), Kelly, Steven, Andrea, Dylan e tanti altri, sono entrati nel cuore di tanti spettatori. 
Soprattutto Brandon (Jason Priestley) e Dylan (Luke Perry),Â i due protagonisti maschili, hanno fatto sognare migliaia di ragazze e riempito di incubi migliaia di ragazzi. Strano a dirsi, la cosa brucia ancora. Per questo i tre infingardi di Plastic Horizons insieme a Marta hanno deciso di sfidare la voce italiana di Brandon, Marco Guadagno (nonchÃ© del Puffo Quattrocchi, di Matthew Broderick nei suoi film anni 80 e di tanti altri tra cui una menzione dâ€™onore merita anche il mitico Serge di Beverly Hills Cop)Â sul suo stesso terreno. 
La sfida si svolgerÃ  per le strade assolate di Beverly Hills, tra palme e spiagge, complice il gioco da tavolo ufficiale di Beverly Hills 90210 e tanta fantasia. 
Ad accompagnarli in questo viaggio ci saranno tutti i protagonisti del telefilm che dal passato guideranno i nostri avventurieri. 
Chi vincerÃ  la sfida Beverly Hills 90210?

Un grande grazie a Marco Guadagno per averci fatto compagnia!
